{{other uses|Oktoberfest (disambiguation)}} [[File:Dancers at Oktoberfest.jpg|thumb|right|Dancers perform at Oktoberfest Zinzinnati]] [[File:Brat Eating Contest at Oktoberfest Zinzinnati.jpg|thumb|right|Crowds enjoy the World's Largest Brat Eating Contest at Oktoberfest Zinzinnati 2012.]] [[File:World's Largest Chicken Dance.jpg|thumb|right|More than 30,000 participated in the World's Largest Chicken Dance in 2015, led by former Bengals quarterback Ken Anderson]] [[File:Oktoberfest Stein Hoist.jpg|thumb|right|Drew and Nick Lachey of 98 Degrees participate in the Sam's Adams Stein Hoisting Championship at Oktoberfest Zinzinnati 2014]] '''Oktoberfest Zinzinnati''' is an annual weekend [[festival]] in the city of [[Cincinnati]], Ohio. Based on the original [[Germany|German]] [[Oktoberfest]], it is billed as the largest [[Oktoberfest celebrations|Oktoberfest celebration]] in the United States.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.fodors.com/world/north-america/usa/ohio/cincinnati/review-150075.html | title=Oktoberfest-Zinzinnati | publisher=Fodor's Travel | accessdate=7 April 2014}}</ref> First held in 1976, it attracts an estimated 500,000 visitors every year in late September.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://myfountainsquare.com/event/oktoberfest-zinzinnati-2/ | title=Oktoberfest-Zinzinnati | publisher=Fountain Square | accessdate=7 April 2014}}</ref> It is held along six blocks of [[Downtown Cincinnati]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oktoberfestzinzinnati.com/okt.aspx?menu_id=256&id=8468 | title=What is Oktoberfest Zinzinnati? | publisher=Cincinnati USA Regional Chamber | accessdate=7 April 2014}}</ref> As of 2016, Oktoberfest is held on 3rd Street to clear room for [[Cincinnati Streetcar]] operations.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bizjournals.com/cincinnati/news/2016/07/19/oktoberfest-zinzinnati-moving-to-new-location.html | title=Oktoberfest Zinzinnati moving to new location | work=Cincinnati Business Journal | date=19 July 2016 | accessdate=25 July 2016 | author=Brownfield, Andy}}</ref>
Oktoberfest Zinzinnati claimed the world record for the largest [[Chicken Dance]] in 1994, with over 48,000 participants. It also boasts approximately 87,542 [[Mettwurst|mett]]s, 80,500 [[Bratwurst|brat]]s, 64,000 sauerkraut balls, 56,250 sausages, 24,640 [[potato pancake]]s, 20,000 cream puffs, 16,002 [[strudel]], 6,000 jumbo pickles, {{convert|3600|lb}} of [[sauerkraut]], {{convert|1875|lb}} of German potato salad, {{convert|702|lb}} of [[Limburger]] cheese, 700 pigtails, 400 [[pickled pigs feet]], and 23,004 [[soft pretzel]]s{{spaced ndash}} including giant {{convert|6|lb|adj=on|spell=in}} pretzels made by Servatii Pastry Shop.<ref> *{{cite web | url=http://www.oktoberfestzinzinnati.com/okt.aspx?menu_id=256&id=8478 | title=Annual Oktoberfest Zinzinnati is Steeped in Tradition | publisher=Cincinnati USA Regional Chamber | accessdate=7 April 2014}} *{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2u0CAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=PA176#v=onepage&q&f=false | title=Prosit! | publisher=Cincinnati Magazine | author=Tate, Skip | year=Sep 1999 | pages=176}}</ref>
